                        </a></div></div><ol class="senses_multiple" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="avon_sng_1" sensenum="1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">any of three rivers with the same name in south-west England. The longest of these flows through <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/warwick" title="Warwick definition"><span class="ndv">Warwick</span></a> and <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/stratford-upon-avon" title="Stratford-upon-Avon definition"><span class="ndv">Stratford-upon-Avon</span></a>. Shakespeare, who was born at Stratford, is sometimes called the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/bard" title="Bard definition"><span class="ndv">Bard</span></a> of Avon.</span></span>          <div id="ring-links-box">
